          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "olzWk",
          "name": "blogArticle",
          "width": 780,
          "stroke": {
            "thickness": {
              "top": 1
            },
            "fill": "#1F2430"
          },
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 18,
          "padding": [
            20,
            0,
            0,
            0
          ],
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "CtDbE",
              "name": "p1",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "It all starts with a Drop. The idea was simple: one place to build gear lists for shoots, backed by a user-driven database of camera, lighting, grip, and sound equipment that people are actually using in the field.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "jDjx7",
              "name": "p2",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "During prep, I always struggled with gear lists. They were repetitive, time-consuming, and often became stale the moment someone changed a package. Spreadsheets got the job done, but collaboration was clunky and context was usually lost in comments and side messages.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "rXkHv",
              "name": "imgA",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 8,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "cornerRadius": 14,
                  "id": "ewTkK",
                  "fill": {
                    "type": "image",
                    "enabled": true,
                    "url": "image-4.png",
                    "mode": "fill"
                  },
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "height": 390
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "BwB0o",
                  "fill": "#94A3B8",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Shootdrop dashboard view used during live prep.",
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "rgYQK",
              "name": "p3",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "I built the backend as a Node.js GraphQL API with MongoDB for structured gear data, and AWS S3 for media and file handling. On the frontend, Next.js and TailwindCSS helped move quickly, while Apollo Client made data fetching and state management predictable.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "CSwYS",
              "name": "imgB",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 8,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "cornerRadius": 14,
                  "id": "bU2Rt",
                  "fill": {
                    "type": "image",
                    "enabled": true,
                    "url": "image-3.png",
                    "mode": "fill"
                  },
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "height": 360
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "ewmEx",
                  "fill": "#94A3B8",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Planning flow focused on fast list creation and revision clarity.",
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "gqWfG",
              "name": "p4",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "What mattered most wasn’t just shipping features, but making the workflow feel obvious under pressure. The product needed to support fast prep decisions, reduce repeated manual work, and stay flexible when lists changed late in production.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "mDHgX",
              "name": "p5",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "One of the biggest design choices was keeping creation lightweight. Instead of forcing users through complex setup screens, the flow starts from a single action and progressively reveals detail only when needed.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "36JiW",
              "name": "p6",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Early feedback from filmmakers has been extremely useful. Teams responded well to the speed of list creation, but surfaced opportunities around filtering, duplicate detection, and better visibility into package changes between revisions.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "xw8Hb",
              "name": "imgC",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 8,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "cornerRadius": 14,
                  "id": "c286q",
                  "fill": {
                    "type": "image",
                    "enabled": true,
                    "url": "image-5.png",
                    "mode": "fill"
                  },
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "height": 320
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "gs2Ro",
                  "fill": "#94A3B8",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Catalog view sourced from community-submitted gear entries.",
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "RTeR9",
              "name": "p7",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The next phase is focused on tightening collaboration: clearer ownership, better handoff states, and practical guardrails that prevent accidental list drift during fast-moving prep windows.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "9DvGf",
              "name": "p8",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Shootdrop is still evolving, but it already proves the core point: prep tools should reduce friction, not add ceremony. The goal is to keep it practical, readable, and trustworthy when production pressure is high.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
