        },
        {
          "type": "frame",
          "id": "VuFEU",
          "name": "blogArticle",
          "width": 780,
          "stroke": {
            "thickness": {
              "top": 1
            },
            "fill": "#1F2430"
          },
          "layout": "vertical",
          "gap": 18,
          "padding": [
            20,
            0,
            0,
            0
          ],
          "children": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "r2YW5",
              "name": "p1",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Most workflow tools fail for the same reason: they assume users have time to think. In reality, people are often moving fast, context-switching, and making decisions with incomplete information. This post outlines how I approach interface design when clarity matters more than novelty.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "jl1At",
              "name": "p2",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "The first principle is to remove avoidable decisions. If the system already knows enough to provide a strong default, it should. Every extra dropdown, optional field, or setup step adds friction, and friction compounds quickly when a team repeats the same task all week.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "f7UiZ",
              "name": "imgA",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 8,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "cornerRadius": 14,
                  "id": "Dg9c0",
                  "fill": {
                    "type": "image",
                    "enabled": true,
                    "url": "DSCF3945.jpg",
                    "mode": "fill"
                  },
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "height": 390
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "UO2Gu",
                  "fill": "#94A3B8",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Early exploration focused on hierarchy before visual styling.",
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "5Jt5O",
              "name": "p3",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "I start by mapping the core loop: what users need to do, what can block them, and what information must stay visible at each step. Once that loop is stable, layout choices become much easier. Sections can then be structured around intent instead of feature lists.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "BKmyB",
              "name": "imgB",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 8,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "cornerRadius": 14,
                  "id": "R4CPt",
                  "fill": {
                    "type": "image",
                    "enabled": true,
                    "url": "IMG_9908.JPG",
                    "mode": "fill"
                  },
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "height": 360
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "B6ZKA",
                  "fill": "#94A3B8",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Wireframes used to test sequence, speed, and comprehension.",
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "uy1X8",
              "name": "p4",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Typography does most of the heavy lifting. Heading scale signals priority, body size optimizes reading comfort, and spacing creates a predictable rhythm. When typography is coherent, users scan faster and make fewer mistakes because the page explains itself.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "qer9F",
              "name": "p5",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "I also avoid decorative interaction where possible. Motion should confirm state changes, not entertain. If an animation slows down interpretation or competes with the main task, it’s noise. In high-pressure tools, calm feedback beats cleverness every time.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "WpHLq",
              "name": "p6",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "Content strategy is equally important. Labels should be specific, status text should be plain language, and errors should explain recovery, not just failure. The goal is not to sound smart. The goal is to help someone continue working without breaking focus.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "frame",
              "id": "6Q6Bs",
              "name": "imgC",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "layout": "vertical",
              "gap": 8,
              "children": [
                {
                  "type": "rectangle",
                  "cornerRadius": 14,
                  "id": "TRcMf",
                  "fill": {
                    "type": "image",
                    "enabled": true,
                    "url": "IMG_20211013_165515.jpg",
                    "mode": "fill"
                  },
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "height": 320
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "id": "G6qAg",
                  "fill": "#94A3B8",
                  "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
                  "width": "fill_container",
                  "content": "Component library pass ensuring consistency across repeated views.",
                  "fontFamily": "Geist",
                  "fontSize": 12,
                  "fontWeight": "normal"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "O0usk",
              "name": "p7",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "One practical technique that keeps interfaces readable is progressive disclosure: show the minimum required to move forward, then reveal detail on demand. This keeps screens light for experienced users while still supporting deeper context when someone needs it.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "id": "cR7CB",
              "name": "p8",
              "fill": "#D1D5DB",
              "textGrowth": "fixed-width",
              "width": "fill_container",
              "content": "When a product feels effortless, it usually means someone removed hundreds of tiny points of confusion. That is the work I care about most: designing systems that stay clear when people are busy, under pressure, and trying to do good work quickly.",
              "lineHeight": 1.75,
              "fontFamily": "Geist",
              "fontSize": 16,
              "fontWeight": "normal"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
